Notes: Broad ride through woodland.  Woodland to the west largely cleared and thinned c15 years ago with much Rubus, Rosa and Corylus regeneration.  Less dense to the east.

This part of the wood was cleared and thinned c15 years ago, leaving dense, regenerating, hedge-like rows of Prunus spinosa, Salix cinerea, Rubus etc, with intervening areas dominated by Carex pendula, Calamagrostis etc.  Quercus robur planted.
Shrub layer cleared c15 years ago, ash canopy thinned.  Dense regeneration of Rosa, Rubus and Corylus coppice.  Quercus planted.
Plot includes a small glade within Corylus coppice with Fraxinus and Quercus standards.
Mixed coppice, some recently cut, but poor regrowth.  Much fallen timber from large old pollards, one massive Fraxinus pollard within the plot.
Plot on the edge of a broad ride with dry W8c to the west.  The ride is mown with an odd grassland vegetation dominated by Holcus lanatus, |Elymus repens, Carex hirta and Ranunculus repens.
Woodland edge with abundant suckering Ulmus, much of which is dead.  Fraxinus canopy with a poor ground flora.
Abundant suckering Ulmus, scattered Quercus robur.  Monotonous ground flora dominated by Mercurialis.
Woodland edge with abundant suckering Ulmus procera, and planted TiliaXeuropaea.
anthrisus dominated site on (probably) builders' rubbish with added rabbit hutches, dustbins etc
secondary woodland  outside wood bank that encloses that ancient part
Open ground layer dominated by Poa trivialis and Galium aparine.  Less fallen elm than elsewhere
Close to the boundary of the wood.  Ground very uneven with much fallen ash and some dumped rubbish near the edge.  Urtica and Anthriscus dominant.
Ash standards with Crataegus shrub layer.  Diverse ground flora.
Mature hazel coppice with ash standards.
Hazel dominated glade adjacent to stands of large oak and fallen elm.
An impenetrable tangle of fallen elm with regenerating saplings, suckers and Rubus.
Much ash regeneration.  Plenty of dead elm in and around the plot.
Oak and rowan standards with dense Ilex shrub layer.  Carpets of leaf litter with little ground flora.
W16 Ilex wood with occasional Quercus robur and Sorbus aucuparia.  Little ground flora apart from Ilex seedlings.
Dense young Ilex with Ilex and Sorbus aucuparia standards and a very sparse ground flora.  Plot on the edge of an unmade track.
Ilex aquifolium with Quercus robur standards.  Plot includes an unmade track with fringing Rubus.
W15.  Fagus canopy over dense Ilex.  Little ground flora, but dense leaf litter.
Very nice stand of W4.  Betula pubescens dominant with B. pendula.  Ground flora mainly Sphagnum recurvum and other Sphagna with Juncus effusus, Molinia, Deschampsia flexuosa etc.
Edge of silted ditch.  Partly W4, Betula pubescens and Salix cinerea with Sphagnum recurvum; partly open M27, and S9b.  Some recent Rhododendron clearance.
Mature W7b Alnus coppice in the valley of a small stream. Alnus dominant with Ilex where drier.  Species-rich ground flora especially where wet.
Open canopy of tall trees.  No shrub layer or regeneration.
Very open woodland with tall standard oak, larch and beech.  Sparse shrub layer of holly, no field layer, dense leaf litter.
Open holly woodland with planted Pinus nigra and some Quercus robur.  No ground flora.
Holly woodland with scattered Quercus, Sorbus aucuparia, planted chestnut and larch. No ground flora.
This plot dominated by a large sweet chestnut.  Mostly larch woodland with a patchy holly shrub layer.  Poor ground flora with abundant leaf litter.
Holly, beech and oak.  No ground flora with abundant leaf litter.  Bare soiled track through the plot. One large standing dead rowan, and one fallen.
Pine and larch woodland with dense holly shrub layer.  No ground flora, abundant leaf litter.  Much fallen timber of all sizes up to whole trees.
